      "name": "What is the maximum CPF contribution for employees aged 55 and below in 2026?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "For Singapore Citizens and PRs (3rd year onwards) aged 55 and below, the employee contributes 20% and the employer contributes 17% of ordinary wages, capped at the Ordinary Wage ceiling of $6,800 per month. The maximum monthly employee CPF contribution is therefore $1,360."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Do CPF contribution rates change when I turn 55?",
